# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __lt__, __le__, __gt__ across all 8 multiprocessing subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 8 classes x 3 methods = 24 rows.
# __lt__: true only for multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy; false for all others.
# __le__: true only for multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy; false for all others.
# __gt__: true only for multiprocessing.managers._BaseSetProxy; false for all others.
# _BaseSetProxy is the sole outlier — it proxies all three set-ordering operators
# to the managed set object in the server process. BaseListProxy and _BaseDictProxy
# do not proxy ordering operators because Python 3 list comparison is element-wise
# (not proxied) and dict ordering is not defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

